  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle</p><p>Slice your <strong>cauliflower[s]</strong> into 1 steak per person, approx. 3cm thick (use the middle part as it's larger!), reserve the<strong> remaining cauliflower</strong> and discard the leaves</p><p>Deseed your <strong>pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon), cut into large chunks, then crush your <strong>garlic</strong> open by squashing with the side of a knife, discard the skin</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cauliflower-steaks-with-sweet-potato-mash-and-romesco/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>cauliflower steak[s]</strong> to a large piece of <strong>tin foil</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, a knob of <strong>butter </strong>and<strong> </strong>1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Scrunch the foil around the cauliflower to form a tightly sealed parcel and add to a baking tray (or two!) with the <strong>chopped pepper[s]</strong>,<strong> peeled garlic </strong>and a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 15-20 min or until the pepper is slightly charred</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cauliflower-steaks-with-sweet-potato-mash-and-romesco/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut the <strong>remaining cauliflower</strong> into small florets</p><p>Peel and chop your <strong>sweet potato[es]</strong> into small bite-sized pieces</p><p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong> then pat it dry with kitchen paper and set aside until later</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cauliflower-steaks-with-sweet-potato-mash-and-romesco/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped sweet potato</strong> and <strong>cauliflower florets</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> over a high heat and bring to the boil</p><p>Cook for 10-15 min or until fork-tender</p><p>Once done, drain, return them to the pot and cover to keep warm</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cauliflower-steaks-with-sweet-potato-mash-and-romesco/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>flaked almonds </strong>to a<strong> food processor </strong>with <strong>half</strong> your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and your <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>red wine vinegar</strong>,<strong> half </strong>your <strong>dried thyme </strong>(you'll use the rest later!), a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Once the pepper is slightly charred, remove the tray[s] from the oven and transfer the <strong>roasted</strong> <strong>pepper </strong>and<strong> garlic</strong> to the food processor – this is your <strong>romesco mix</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cauliflower-steaks-with-sweet-potato-mash-and-romesco/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Open the <strong>cauliflower parcel[s]</strong>,<strong> </strong>then<strong> </strong>add the <strong>remaining grated Italian hard cheese</strong> and <strong>remaining dried thyme</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Return the tray[s] to the oven and cook, uncovered, for 5 min or until the cauliflower is golden and tender – this is your<strong> cheesy cauliflower steak</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cauliflower-steaks-with-sweet-potato-mash-and-romesco/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, blitz the <strong>romesco mix </strong>until smooth – this is your <strong>romesco sauce</strong></p><p>Return the pot with the drained potato and cauliflower to a low heat with a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Once the butter has melted, mash until smooth – this is your <strong>cauliflower & sweet potato mash</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cauliflower-steaks-with-sweet-potato-mash-and-romesco/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> cauliflower & sweet potato mash </strong>with the<strong> spinach</strong> to the side</p><p>Top with the<strong> romesco sauce </strong>and<strong> cheesy cauliflower steak</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
